Despite CBS claiming the cancellation of The Late Show was "purely a financial decision" and "not related in any way to the show's performance, content or other matters happening at Paramount," some speculated that Paramount's Skydance Media merger ‚Äî which at that point still required approval from the Trump administration ‚Äî may have been a factor.Regardless, Colbert, a longtime Trump critic, didn't hold back in the days after his announcement. He ramped up his coverage of the president's actions, telling him to "go **** yourself" before doubling down on his coverage of Trump's friendship with convicted child sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.4. Jimmy Kimmel being suspended

