Following Kimmel's suspension, John Oliver joined the late night hosts showing their support with a deep dive into exactly what the hell happened. In a must-watch monologue, the Last Week Tonight host lambasted the threatening tactics used by Trump's FCC chair Carr, and appealed directly to Disney CEO Bob Iger, urging him to stand up to parent company ABC using "the only phrase that can genuinely make a weak bully go away...'F*** you. Make me.'"6. Jon Stewart's 'administration compliant' Daily Show monologue

