Another must-watch reaction to Kimmel's suspension was The Daily Show's 23-minute "administration-compliant" monologue from Jon Stewart poking fun at censorship. Facetiously walking on proverbial eggshells, the host referred to Donald Trump as "father" and told the audience to "shut the f*** up" if they reacted negatively to the president ‚Äî even in regard to Trump's comments saying Kimmel was suspended for having "zero talent" instead of threats from FCC chair Carr to Jimmy Kimmel Live! broadcaster ABC.7. Seth Meyers calls Kimmel suspension 'a big moment in our democracy'

