Late Night host Seth Meyers has also been a target of the president this year, and also responded to Kimmel's suspension by ABC with support. In a strong monologue, Meyers took A Closer Look at censorship and free speech in Donald Trump's America."Trump promised to end government censorship and bring back free speech, and he's doing the opposite," said Meyers, calling out Kimmel's suspension. "This is a big moment in our democracy, and we must all stand up for the principles of free expression. There's a reason free speech is in the very First Amendment. It stands above all others."8. Kimmel's record-breaking return monologue

